<TITLE> BIWTA launches training for masters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 27 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority (BIWTA) began a two-day training for launch masters and drivers at Sadarghat Pontoon on Thursday to raise their skills to handle vessels in the middle of nor'westers. "The workshop attempts to provide launch drivers and masters to address their lack of know-how when ships fall upon nor'westers in the middle of their journey," Mohammad Ali Siddique, a BIWTA official told bdnews24.com. A total of 50 launch masters and drivers will receive training on the first day running from 10am until 4pm and 50 others on the second day," Siddique, also BIWTA's senior deputy director said. Every trainee will receive a certificate which will be considered as their extra quality, he said. BIWTA director (conservancy and pilotage) Emdadul Haque inaugurated the workshop at around 10am. Deck & Personal Training Centre official Ashraf Hossain and deck & personal and BIWTA's conservancy and pilotage division's deputy director Fazlur Rahman, among others, were trainers. BIWTA organised such training workshops in 2008 and 2009. bdnews
